news.title: Oberoi Realty to sell 21.74% share in I-Ven Realty to Alpha Wave Ventures for Rs 1,250 crore
news.para: I-Ven is a joint venture company of Oberoi Realty, and the shares of I-Ven are currently held between company and Vikas in equal proportion.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Shops & malls within 500 meters of metro, RRTS to pay special amenities fee now
news.para: UP govt has made provisions for the same in its UP Urban Planning and Development (Assessment, Levy, and Collection of Special Amenity Fee) Rules 2024, and a govt order (GO) in this regard was issued by the state govt.

news.title: Asian Paints completes divestment of Indonesian operations
news.para: APIPL on Thursday completed the divestment of the Indonesia operations by sale of the entire stake held by APIPL in PTAPI & PTAPCI for a consideration of SGD 6.8 million (about Rs 44 crore), Asian Paints said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Etonhurst Capital raises Rs 180 crore as first close of Mumbai redevelopment fund
news.para: The first close of the fund has witnessed participation from family offices, high-net-worth individuals (HNIs) and The Guardian Real Estate Advisory’s family office.

news.title: Online tenant verification rollout in Pune, Mumbai from next month
news.para: Registration department officials on Thursday said the integration would cover 130 police stations in Mumbai city and suburban areas, and 87 police stations in Pune city and rural areas.

news.title: Government to recognise private layout roads, seal illegal constructions in Bengaluru
news.para: “Roads have been developed in private layouts across the city. While we have also worked on their development, land records still show the original owners’ names. These records need to be updated, and private layout roads must be officially recognized as public roads,” he stated.

news.title: Nisus Finance's fund exits from Shapoorji Pallonji Real Estate's subsidiary
news.para: RESO-I had invested Rs 105 crore into senior secured rated listed non-convertible debentures (NCDs) issued by Suvita Real Estate, a subsidiary of SPRE, in January 2024.

news.title: Lucknow development body to launch online portal for land details, verification
news.para: This initiative aims to provide transparent and comprehensive land details, curbing property disputes and fraudulent land sales.

news.title: Three more fraud cases filed against Ansal API's director in Lucknow
news.para: So far, 32 cases have been registered against Ansal API and its owners in various police stations across the city. Shailendra Singh of Indiranagar said he fixed a deal for a villa in Ansal for Rs 64 lakh.

news.title: Residential flats must be registered under apartment ownership act: Karnataka HC
news.para: Justice K S Hemalekha delivered this ruling whilst approving a petition by Saraswathi Prakash and other apartment owners from Parkside Retirement Homes Brigade Orchards Apartment Complex.

news.title: Two new metro corridors set to be built in Gurugram
news.para: Haryana Mass Rapid Transport Corporation (HMRTC) on Thursday invited tenders to prepare detailed project reports (DPR) of the two metro lines.

news.title: Bombay HC upholds closure order of mall operating without environmental nod
news.para: The petitioner company, Grauer and Weil (India) Limited, considers itself above the law and has shown scant regard for environmental concerns, a division bench of Justices M S Sonak and Jitendra Jain said in its order on Wednesday.

news.title: Ravi Puravankara buys 12 commercial properties in Mumbai for Rs 242 crore
news.para: The seller of these 12 commercial units is RockFort Estate Developer Pvt Ltd while the buyer is Ravi Puravankara. These 12 properties, ranging from 6,750 sq ft carpet area to nearly 10,000 sq ft, are located at Andheri, Mumbai.

news.title: Work completed on 20 lakh houses under PMAY in Rajasthan: Agriculture minister
news.para: After the meeting, Union Minister Chouhan emphasized that out of the 24 lakh houses targeted for Rajasthan under the PMAY, work on 20 lakh houses has been completed, while the rest are in progress.

news.title: Haryana CM releases first instalment of Rs 151 crore to eligible families under PMAY-Gramin
news.para: As part of the first instalment, Rs 45,000 was transferred into bank account of each eligible family for house construction, an official statement said.

news.title: Gurugram DC issues order to vacate towers A,B, C of Chintels Paradiso society
news.para: ​The order, issued to implement Section 163 of the Indian Civil Defence Code, requires all three towers to be vacated within 15 days, said Gurugram DC and Chairman of District Disaster Management Authority Ajay Kumar.

news.title: Germany must build 320,000 apartments yearly to meet housing demand: Study
news.para: Authorities granted permits for the building of just under 216,000 apartments in 2024, as Europe's largest economy navigates its worst real-estate crisis in decades, keeping a lid on new construction.

news.title: HC's directives were not violated in granting land use changes: Rajasthan urban minister
news.para: The minister emphasised that amendments to Rajasthan Urban Land Use Change Rules-2010, notified on Feb 24 and Nov 6, 2024, granted full authority to the State-Level Land Use Change Committee for changes in master plans and zonal development plans.

news.title: Goa: GCZMA inspects illegal constructions in Candolim beach's CRZ zone
news.para: Citizens’ group Calangute Constituency Forum (CCF), which lodged the complaint, claimed that the construction is completely illegal and in clear violation of the CRZ Notification and the Environment Protection Act.

news.title: Vadodara civic body launches major crackdown on illegal constructions
news.para: The drive against unauthorised street vendors included the removal of handcarts and other material from the Shastri Bridge area. Four truckloads of material were seized from the location.
